annotationA: Delta-1-Pyrroline-5-carboxylate dehydrogenase 1 is a conserved, nuclear-encoded mitochondrial matrix enzyme. It is a member of the aldehyde dehydrogenase superfamily involved in proline degradation
annotationB: Pyridoxal phosphate binding; glutamate decarboxylase activity; aspartate 1-decarboxylase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: visual behavior; beta-alanine biosynthetic process; uracil catabolic process; developmental pigmentation; carboxylic acid metabolic process
